sentences: Park Ji-hyo (Korean: 박지효; born Park Ji-soo on February 1, 1997), known mononymously as Jihyo, is a South Korean singer.
Jihyo was born on February 1, 1997 in Guri, Gyeonggi Province, South Korea.
She then joined JYP Entertainment as a trainee at the age of eight and trained for ten years before her debut.
During her trainee years, Jihyo was known as the face of Innisfree's teen line with boy band Boyfriend.

In October 2015, Twice officially debuted with the release of their first mini-album, The Story Begins, with the lead single "Like Ooh-Ahh" being the first K-pop debut song to reach 100 million views on YouTube.
